<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Thomson, John. Journal, Mackenzie River, 1800-1802. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0021</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p style="text-align:justify;">gave them drams &amp;<sup>c</sup> &#8211; they paid 17 skins Credits<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Traded 27 skins 1 of Grease, 1 Depouille &amp; 10 of Dried Meat<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Monday the 29<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Gave one of the Indians 18 skins on Credit, &amp; sent the 2 others to the other side of the River to hunt Hares &#8211; the two that are here already I intend to give them their discharge as they are continually playing me for it<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Tuesday the 30<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Severe Cold<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The 2 hunters arrived<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> they brought 44 hares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Wednesday the 31<sup>st</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>he hunters returned to their Snares for the last time as I desired them to raise all their snares in order to give them their discharge<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Early in the morning sent Plante to the other side with 60 Snares for the hunters that are there &#8211; he came back late in the afternoon with his <span style="text-decoration:underline;">face Frozen a little</span><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Thursday the 1<sup>st</sup>  January 1801<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In honor of the Féte expended one flacon of Spirits, and gave half a dozen rings to the Ladies for their New years Gift<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Very Cold day<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Saturday the 3<sup>d</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In the afternoon the 2 hunters arrived<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> they brought 50 hares &amp; all the Snares &#8211; likewise the 2 young Men from the other side arrived<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> they brought 64 hares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Sunday the 4<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The 2 y Men from the other side set<sup>d</sup> to their Snares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[O]</span>ne of the others went away<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> paid him for 294 hares at the rate of 14 p skin &#8211; he traded 4 Pichous<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> 1 beaver capot &amp; 1 orig<sup>l</sup> skin &#8211; gave him 28 skins on Credit<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The other y Man went to set his Snares near hand, as he wishes to remain here untill Martin arrives<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Monday the 5<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The young Man or rather the old for he is no chicken took only 1 hare, he is a Lazy old codger.  I do not expect he will take much more then enough to feed himself, besides he is an Estropie<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Tuesday the 6<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The Estropie took 5 hares.  The 2 hunters from the other side arrived<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> they brought only 18 hares &amp; all the Snares.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Wednesday the 7<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent the 2 y Men to set the Snares in another quarter<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The Estropie killed 7 hares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Thursday the 8<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The y Men took 8 D<sup>o</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Made 85 Candles.  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>hey are the first I made since my arrival here on acc<sup>t</sup> of Grease being a very scarce Article<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Friday the 9<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The y Man took 8 hares &#8211; he raised all the Snares &amp; went away to set them with the other hunters<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
